title: Senior FrontEnd Engineer
description:
About us: VEscape Labs is a technology development firm specializing in cloud technologies. We connect top talent with firms seeking rapid growth and acceleration, turbo-charging their development teams to help them meet strategic goals.


We spark rapid growth and acceleration of strategic cloud initiatives, with deep expertise and boundary-pushing innovation to turbo-charge development teams. We are a magnet and incubator for top technical people, offering comprehensive training programs, a unique hands-on mentorship structure, and an entrepreneurial culture.


Our next team member will be authentic, articulate, and passionate about cloud technologies and is unafraid to roll up their sleeves and dive deep into the unknowns, using their expertise to identify opportunities to increase the overall capabilities of VEscape Labs internally and for our clients.


At VEscape Labs, you will have the opportunity to engage with systems that are at the cutting edge of technology. We allow our employees to build from the ground up and make an impact across the organization.


What You Will Do:

  • Our ideal candidate will understand the value of teamwork and love living in the in-between of project delivery and managing high-trust client relationships. We are looking for the right fit with our rapidly growing organization and will invest in training.


Your knowledge, skills, and abilities:

  • 3+ years of experience in developing cloud-native applications.

  • Experience in front-end development (familiarity and exposure with full-stack

    development is desired but not required).

  • Proficient in JavaScript and Angular. Experience with Typescript is ideal. Experience with React is a plus.

  • Proficient in developing applications on the Google Cloud Platform suite of products and services is ideal.

  • Familiar with unit testing and test-driven development (TDD).

  • Familiar with the scrum process and Git.

  • Experience establishing CI/CD pipelines to accelerate software delivery.

  • Background in professional services/consulting.

  • Eager to work in a teamwork/collaborative environment.

  • You will solve real-world problems and will work on projects that matter to the business, delivering software as part of a cross-functional team composed of software engineers, designers and product managers.

  • Get hands-on exposure with cutting-edge technology from managers, mentors, and fellow team members.

  • Deliver business value for customers in teams committed to the practices and principles of UCD (User-Centered Design), and Lean Product Management.

  • Familiar with the scrum process and Git.

  • Experience establishing CI/CD pipelines to accelerate software delivery.

  • Background in professional services/consulting.

  • Strong communication skills.

  • Eager to work in a teamwork/collaborative environment.

  • Depending on your background, interest, and technical alignment to the various areas of Google Cloud Platform technology stack, you will be working on development and modernization projects as part of the 66degrees Cloud Native Application Development and Modernization team.


Why VEscape Labs?

We are committed to creating an inclusive environment for our team. If you have a special need that requires accommodation, please let your recruiter know.


We currently offer the following benefits:

  • Access to private medical insurance through Axa
  • Life insurance policy via Sura Seguros
  • 30-day Christmas bonus and a monthly technology stipend
  • Contribution of 8% of the employee's salary to a savings fund
  • Flexible vacation policy that allows you to manage your schedule and rest and recharge when you need to
  • Family-friendly benefits, including 16 weeks off for Maternity leave, 8 weeks off for non-birthing parent leave, and employer-paid short-term and long-term disability.
  • Support on individual development through certifications, continued learning, conferences, and more

We value a diverse workforce and a culture of inclusivity and belonging. All employment decisions shall be made without regard to age, race, creed, color, religion, gender, national origin, ancestry, disability status, veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, citizenship status or any other basis as protected by federal, state, or local law. VEscape Labs is an Equal Opportunity Employer.

title: Inside Tele Sales
description:
Must be motivated and driven by money!

compensation: 12K Base Plus Commission
employment type: Full-Time

California Based Same Day Delivery Company is looking for a SELF STARTER that will BUILD and GROW a SALES team. It STARTS with you.... Our goal is to provide economical fast and friendly freight-delivery service 24/7/365.. This is supported through our Queretaro call center.

The right person can average 30K - 60k MNX PER MONTH.... IT IS MORE THAN A FULL TIME JOB- WORK HARDER PLAY HARDER ENVIORMENT!

We are looking for high energy sales closer who can sell this B2B Transportation Service over phone, Zoom... Email or flights to Cali!!!

You must be an enthusiastic and well-polished sales professional. Applicants will need the ability to exercise an incredible amount of tenacity to succeed in this competitive market. This position is responsible for identifying, establishing relationships and selling our small package to trailer loads of Freight delivery service to all industries.

This is a great opportunity for a self-starter, self-motivated, sales professional looking for an opportunity to grow a business within a business. Ideal person is one who is accustomed to making cold calls, navigating to the decision-makers, setting appointments, conducting online demos, and closing business.

Responsibilities

  • Cold calling to generate new sales leads and navigate and identify key decision-makers.
  • Manage the entire sales cycle: conducting sales calls and meetings, negotiating contracts, and providing customers with valuable insights and offerings as part of an on-going, consultative relationship.
  • Successfully close new business through relationship-based selling
  • Master the ability to evangelize the 247 Delivery Services culture and story.
  • Achieve and exceed quarterly quotas.
  • Align our services to provide a solution to all prospect business client's needs.
  • Proactively keep abreast of our industry and the technology landscape to ensure you are a trusted resource to prospects and customers.
  • Must be self-motivated, eager to learn and succeed.

Requirements

  • Proven stable past employment or school from individual.
  • Professional telephone manner (95 % ENGLISH FLUENCY IS A MUST)
  • Excellent presentation skills
  • Strong written and verbal skills (100 % ENGLISH FLUENCY IS A MUST)
  • Demonstrated leadership ability (we want natural leaders)
  • Track record of opening new accounts via phone calls, referrals, and other methods. Tenacious hunger to win business and close deals.
  • Highly organized and strong time management skills
  • Ability to work in a fast paced, changing environment with minimal direction.
  • INDEPENDENT-HOME BASE REMOTE JOB- CONTRACT

Preferred Qualifications

  • 2-year degree
  • 6 months minimum inside sales with B2B sales experience
  • Proficient with Microsoft Office products and CRM systems
  • Understanding about social media, search engine optimization, search engine marketing, local search fundamentals and web development
  • Experience selling Transportation or 3rd partly logistics is a plus
  • Consistent over-achievement in past positions
  • Proven prospecting and sales cycle management skills
  • WANTS TO GROW and POTENTIALY MANANGE THE TEAM

Work Remotely

  • YES

Job Types: Full-time, Part-time, Contract, Commission
Contract length: 6 months
Part-time hours: 30 per week

Pay: $12,000.00 - $50,000.00 per month

Work Location: Remote

Expected Start Date: 16/07/2023

title: Real Estate Lead manager
description:
Lead Manager Job Description

Real Estate Lead Manager

Job Type

● Part Time-time

● Remote

Qualifications

● Willingness to learn

● Understand Batch dialer & Podio

● Excellent negotiator

No resume needed: Submit a One-Way interview Indeed requests. I will not consider applications who do not submit the one-way interview.

This is a performance-based position. We have an immediate opening for a highly ambitious and purpose-driven individual to join and grow with our team!

1. Pay structure will depend on experience level. This will be a hybrid of hourly & commission based pay.

- Salary: $5-6 an hour plus bonus on every deal closed.

- Commission: All capped at $1,500

- Wholesale: 5% of wholesale fee

- Listing: 3% of 3% commission

- If I buy: 1% purchase price

2. Your primary responsibility is to qualify leads, negotiate, & see them through contract If this is not something you are comfortable with doing, this is probably not the right position for you.

3. Must be OK with weekly training meetings as well as morning check-ins to get a game plan together and answer any questions you might have.

4. No benefits

Responsibilities Include:

  • Responding to inbound leads and prospects via multiple channels (SMS, SEO, Cold Calling, direct mail, etc.). Some leads may call off the clock, take the calls.
  • Put the property under contract

Manage pipeline of prospects and follow-up on leads in a timely manner

  • Monitor the sales process and document follow-up by tracking all interaction details in the
  • Call realtors
  • Analyze & comp deals

CRM

● Be willing to communicate with leads outside of work hours

● Respond to inbound leads from all lead sources

● Talk with distressed sellers that want to sell their house. Build rapport with them and overcome objections.

● Open and willing to learn & improve on all softwares used at the company on your own time

● Assess comparables, property value, and condition through research and MLS

● Daily prospecting activities using various mediums as identified by the company

● Maintain company records and tracking systems

● Meet and exceed monthly quotas

Bonus pay after 90 days if KPI’s are met.

Do not apply if you're not fearless and don’t enjoy talking to people.

Apoyo compensatorio: $800.00 (Ochocientos pesos al mes más bono de productividad)

Prestaciones adicionales:

  • Descuentos y precios preferenciales
  • Trabajo de Lunes a Viernes
  • Trabajo desde casa (Home Office)
  • A partir del 3er mes se te paga un Servicio de SPA, una vez por bimestre; para recibir servicios de Fisioterapia, o Faciales o Masaje relajante o descontracturante.
  • A partir del 3er mes, se te paga $200 pesos mensuales, para apoyo a gastos ya sea de telefonía, o Luz, o Internet.
  • Oportunidad de asistir a cursos de capacitación presenciales, con valor curricular, pagadas por la empresa
  • Oportunidad de crecimiento dentro de la empresa

Requerimientos obligatorios:

Debes contar en tu domicilio con Computadora o Laptop, con servicio de Internet y teléfono. Puede ser fijo o celular con plan básico

Requisitos:

  • Mayor de 18 años
  • Saber trabajar con rapidez
  • Manejo de paquetería office
  • Contar con facilidad de palabra
  • Con buena ortografía y redacción
  • Habilidades de comunicación (Gusto por comunicar y buen trato hacia la gente)
  • Escolaridad mínima de preparatoria, o técnico o estudiante universitario (Enfocado a humanidades, administrativo o contable)
  • Responsable, organizado, comprometido, honesto, con iniciativa, autónomo y paciente

title: Desarrollador Full Stack
description:
Estamos buscando un talentoso Desarrollador de Software para unirse a nuestro equipo y colaborar en la integración de nuestro software con otras plataformas mediante nuestra API.

Responsabilidades principales:

  • Trabajar en colaboración con el equipo de desarrollo para diseñar e implementar soluciones de integración de software mediante el uso de nuestra API.
  • Realizar análisis y pruebas exhaustivas de la funcionalidad de la API, identificar posibles problemas y proponer soluciones efectivas.
  • Colaborar con otros equipos internos y externos para garantizar una integración fluida y exitosa con sistemas de terceros.
  • Documentar y mantener actualizada la documentación técnica relacionada con la integración de software y la API.
  • Investigar y mantenerse actualizado sobre las mejores prácticas y tendencias en el campo de la integración de software y los servicios web.

Requisitos:

  • Experiencia demostrable en el desarrollo e integración de software utilizando APIs.
  • Conocimientos sólidos de lenguajes de programación como Java, Python o JavaScript.
  • Familiaridad con protocolos y formatos comunes como REST, JSON y XML.
  • Experiencia en el manejo de herramientas de integración continua y control de versiones (por ejemplo, Git).
  • Capacidad para analizar y resolver problemas técnicos de manera efectiva.
  • Habilidades de comunicación efectiva y capacidad para colaborar con equipos multidisciplinarios.
  • Excelentes habilidades de organización y atención al detalle.

Sobre ti:

  • Te gusta trabajar en equipo: te sientes cómodo ayudando a tus compañeros de equipo, compartiendo tus conocimientos, revisando su código y pidiendo consejo.
  • Te centras en la calidad: escribes buen código, con métodos de test. Entiendes que la calidad del producto es un valor fundamental de un buen programador.
  • Tienes una mentalidad centrada en el usuario: sabes que la única razón por la que escribimos código es para ayudar a los usuarios finales.
  • Tienes iniciativa: te gusta proponer nuevas hipótesis y ser responsable de construirlas, implementarlas y validarlas.

title: Sales Representative
description:
We are looking for a highly motivated Sales Manager with perfect spoken and written English to join our team at WAcademy. You can work remotely from anywhere you like, as long as you have a good, stable internet connection and a computer! Full sales training and a great working environment will be provided for you.

If you are also results-oriented, thrive in a start-up environment, are keen on experiments and passionate about technology, you just might be the right person. Join our team!

Responsibilities:

  • Expanding our client base through proactive outreach via phone and email. You will be provided with a list of potential clients who have already expressed interest in our services, thus eliminating the need for cold calling
  • Using different working tools and keeping CRM data up-to-date
  • Implementing and overlooking an efficient sales strategy
  • Building customer relationships – earning their loyalty and trust
  • Closing sales with consultative selling approaches
  • Analyzing and understanding customer needs and pain points to provide the best possible solution
  • Working collaboratively with the internal product development team
  • Ensure the customer is treated fairly and receives excellent service according to industry and company guidelines

Requirements:

  • Proven experience in sales or negotiation (if you have no experience, we will really appreciate your effort to convince us)
  • A go-getter attitude and strong communication skills
  • Perfect spoken and written English
  • Working knowledge of Microsoft Office tools
  • Be eager to learn fast and grow as a sales guru.
  • Be confident and well organized; also have a professional attitude towards responsibilities and work
  • Problem solving and creative thinking skills
  • Be ambitious to generate substantial earnings by conquering foreign markets
  • Strong motivation to work in B2B sales and reach set targets

Bonus points:

  • Ability to work with minimal supervision
  • Ability to adapt to a changing environment
  • Have organized, results-oriented and challenge-driven personality
  • Experience in Customer Service, Sales, Project Management, Web Development or Digital Marketing will be an advantage

Company offers:

  • Fixed monthly salary 460€ + Commissions. Our sales managers on average earn between €700-1000/per month based on their sales performance.
  • Monthly bonus based on your performance.
  • Flexible hours & opportunity to work fully remotely.
  • Friendly and supportive team.
  • Regular company events.
  • Internal employee referral program.
  • Career growth, progression, and learning development resources.

About WAcademy

WAcademy Ltd. is an EdTech company based in five offices across Europe. Founded in 2017, the company offers professional training and real-life work experience to ambitious web designers via the WAcademy internship program. Simultaneously, the company works with SMEs that, in return for providing interns with exciting projects, get to enjoy free web design services. In 2023, WAcademy changed the game by inviting university students into the internship program. This will enable even more aspiring web designers to build professional portfolios and even more SMEs to bring their businesses online. With over 30,000 websites built thus far and plans to double the number by the end of the year, WAcademy is on track to becoming the #1 internship platform in the world.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $13,000.00 - $19,000.00 per month

Application Question(s):

  • Why do you want to work with us?
  • Are you comfortable working in remote work setting?

Education:

  • Bachelor's (Preferred)

Experience:

  • Sales: 1 year (Required)

Language:

  • English (Required)
  • English perfectly (Required)

Work Location: Remote

description:

  • Prospección de clientes B2B, empresas «medianas», que pagan mensualmente entre MX $100,000 y MX$ 350,000 en cada uno de sus recibos de CFE para ofrecer una solución de energía solar fotovoltaica.

Requisitos:
  • Historial comprobado en industrias donde los clientes son principalmente del sector Comercial e Industrial (C&I) con empresas serias y robustas, de tamaño mediano/grande, y con experiencia probada vendiéndoles servicios o maquinaria de calidad; por ejemplo, soluciones de energía renovable, sistemas de almacenamiento de energía), equipos industriales (por ejemplo, sistemas HVAC, maquinaria de fabricación de alta tecnología), servicios de infraestructura (por ejemplo, transmisión o distribución de energía), o en sectores donde la comprensión del uso y el costo de la energía es clave (por ejemplo, consultoría de eficiencia energética, auditoría energética).
  • Buena relación con gente de compras o de dirección de las empresas.
  • Habilidades de comunicación: Los candidatos deben poseer excelentes habilidades interpersonales y tener un historial de éxito en la creación y gestión de relaciones comerciales.
  • La experiencia en ventas B2B y una capacidad demostrada para comunicar de manera efectiva temas complejos sería una ventaja.
  • Profesionalismo: Se requiere un alto nivel de profesionalismo, ya que los agentes estarán representando los valores y estándares de nuestra empresa. Se prefiere experiencia en roles donde se requería un alto grado de confianza y profesionalismo.
  • Orientación a resultados: Es altamente deseable un sólido historial de logro de objetivos de ventas u otros resultados medibles en sus roles anteriores. Los candidatos deben ser autónomos y estar motivados por la perspectiva de ganar tarifas basadas en el éxito.
  • Fiabilidad: Dada la importancia crítica de la confianza en nuestro negocio, los candidatos deben haber demostrado altos niveles de integridad en sus roles pasados. Es importante tener una reputación positiva dentro de su industria o red.
  • Comprensión del sector energético: Aunque no necesitan ser expertos en PPA, es importante tener una comprensión básica del sector energético y sus desafíos. Los roles pasados en industrias relacionadas con la gestión de la energía, la eficiencia energética o la energía renovable serían ventajosos. Se proporcionará la formación necesaria para entender y presentar nuestras soluciones de PPA.
  • Disponibilidad para viajar si lo requiere.
Nota: Esta vacante es un rol freelance (comisionista) y puede estar laborando actualmente.

title: Associate Project Manager
description:
Together we are powering the future of Higher Education:
Here at Ellucian, we are motivated by a mission ~ the power of education to transform lives and change the world. We are the global market leader in EdTech for Higher Education, serving more than 2,900 customers and reaching over 26 million students in 50+ countries. We are dedicated to helping Higher Ed thrive by transforming their institutions to agile, digitally connected campuses that enable student success.

About the Opportunity:

We have an exciting opportunity for an ambitious, energetic Associate Project Manager (APM) to make a difference and shape the line of business in a growing global organization. The Associate Project Manager (APM) role will be a member of a team of project managers in our COO Enablement team, and will be located in the Pueblo, Mexico office.

The APM will report to the COO Enablement, Program Manager and will be responsible to serve as the Enablement liaison to an assigned division within COO. In this capacity, the APM will own responsibility to gather, inventory, track, and report status on the enablement activities required by their assigned division(s) within the COO. In the course of this work, the APM will be responsible to track work being done by the COO Enablement team and other internal Ellucian teams to create new or inventory/curate existing content to help facilitate enablement and learning across the COO. When necessary, the APM will be required to escalate concerns or status impediments in enablement activities or content production. The APM must be a strong communicator, able to anticipate risks and help identify potential mitigation strategies when necessary. Given the COO Enablement team will be a small team to start, there may be other duties assigned to the APM as needed and in alignment with the skills and talents they bring to COO Enablement and Ellucian more broadly.

Where you will make an impact

  • Drive project definition and iterate until projects are defined to support the business case and desired business value.
  • Manage all aspects of multiple workstreams, consolidating information and content where appropriate.
  • Lead project activities in a transparent and productive way, applying standard project management practices where appropriate.
  • Define and design the enablement needs for the assigned COO division(s).
  • Work with the COO divisional leader(s) and Enablement leaders to prioritize the enablement needs by solution, by role for each assigned COO division.
  • Collaborate with other APMs, Program Management, and other key Enablement team members to ensure minimal duplication of efforts and to maximize shared content where appropriate and available.
  • Provide weekly status reports to ensure assigned divisional area’s/areas’ work is progressing as needed.
  • Proactively manage project issues and risks.
  • Incorporate change management as a key element for each project.
  • Ensure projects are delivered on-time/on budget and exceeding stakeholders' expectations.
  • Lead projects from beginning to end, from project inception through delivery.
  • Provide thought leadership to further develop and maintain Enablement templates, processes, and programs.
  • Demonstrate an ongoing commitment to professional growth in program/project management, enablement, customer success and other key areas within the COO.

What you will bring

  • Is proactive, works hard, and above all else get things done.
  • Must be creative, relationship management, and teamwork focused.
  • Has successfully managed multiple projects in a matrixed environment with strong influencing skills.
  • Demonstrated ability to partner with the business line to craft solutions.
  • Experience in managing a broad range of technology projects and demonstrated learning agility.
  • 1+ years related work experience in a company or department with a heavy emphasis on technology.
  • 1+ years direct work experience in a project management capacity.
  • Familiarity with project management software, such as Smartsheet, Excel, SharePoint, and MS Office.
  • Ability to ascertain communication styles of team members and contractors who come from a broad spectrum of disciplines.
  • Possess strong written and oral communication skills.
What makes #Ellucianlife:
  • Comprehensive health coverage: family major medical expenses, dental and life insurance.
  • Christmas bonus 30 days
  • Saving fund
  • Monthly food coupon
  • 15 workdays vacation
  • Thrive Flex Program that allows you to contribute towards your health, financial or learning interests
  • 5 charitable days to support the community that supports us
  • Diversity and inclusion programs that promote employee resource groups such as: Women in Technology, Pride and Go Green to name a few.
  • Parental leave
  • Employee referral bonuses to encourage the addition of great new people to the team
  • We Foster a learning culture with:
    • Tuition Reimbursement Assistance
    • Professional development opportunities
